==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Biuret
<hw>Bi"u*ret</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>bi-</ets> + <ets>urea</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A
white, crystalline, nitrogenous substance, <chform>C2O2N3H5</chform>,
formed by heating urea. It is intermediate between urea and cyanuric
acid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

